    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Any form of twill in which the direction of the diagonal lines is reversed over groups of picks, or over groups of ends.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000043641/Burnham, Warp and Weft (1980)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Cualquier forma de sarga en la cual la dirección de las líneas diagonales es revertida sobre grupos de golpes de lanzadera o sobre grupos de extremos.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Elke keperstof waarbij de richting van de diagonale lijnen wordt omgekeerd in groepjes inslagdraden of in groepjes scheringdraden, waardoor een visgraatpatroon ontstaat.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
